ate that have only made things worse for the people of both worlds. As harsh as the parting scene may have been depicted to the viewers, both have only found scant comfort in being united with their son one last time, being finally freed from their respective prisons by the said meeting with their son and lastly in finding faith in Amata that he will save the worlds from their mistakes which they are denied from correcting themselves.</span></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">However this does not stop Alicia from being a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini">Karma Houdini</a> as Kagura the other half of their son that Alicia knew about but did <em>nothing</em> before she fell into that slumber was treated horribly by Mykage and had his life entirely ruined because of her keeping quiet. The fact that she never tries to see the other half of their son despite knowing about him makes her actions not that justified.</span></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"><strong>Mykage</strong> is this. The worst he got hit with is that he a heart shaped attacked used against him and his plans foiled. But now he is a part of the man he loves and hates for all <em>eternity</em> just like he always wanted. He even describes it as being warm inside Fudou.</span></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Possibly Kagura as well. He's killed nearly a dozen Neo-Deava students, and tried to kill Amata multiple times, yet is seemingly accepted by Neo-Deava without much grief. Granted, he did seem to save Zessica, and was essential in winning the final battle, not to mention we never see the circumstances to his being on the island with everybody else, just that nobody payed him much mind during the final scene, where everyone (Kagura included) was rejoicing Amata and Mikono's return.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KilledOffForReal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KilledOffForReal">Killed Off for Real</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Jin at the end of Episode 13. Also Shrade in episode 23 and then Izumo and Alicia in the next episode.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LeeroyJenkins" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LeeroyJenkins">Leeroy Jenkins</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Deconstruction" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Deconstruction">Deconstructed</a> in Episode 18. Zessica's actions <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> end up getting Mix kidnapped.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LetsYouAndHimFight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LetsYouAndHimFight">Let's You and Him Fight</a>: The OVA's promotional video features Aquarion Evol and Solar Aquarion duking it. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Turns out to be little more than Kagura and Apollo <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LeeroyJenkins" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LeeroyJenkins">doing their</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BloodKnight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BloodKnight">thing.</a></span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LiteralSplitPersonality" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LiteralSplitPersonality">Literal Split Personality</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Kagura is actually the "dark side" of Amata who was split by Mykage in order to use him for his revenge.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LogicBomb" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LogicBomb">Logic Bomb</a>: During his first mock exercise, instead